00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:04.400 align:middle line:84%
because we're going to talk
a lot about science today--

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:07.100 align:middle line:84%
but what has been, for you
personally, the highlight

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:08.360 align:middle line:90%
of what you've done?

00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:11.020 align:middle line:10%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Sub-quantum
kinetics, the physics theory

00:01:11.020 --> 00:01:12.975 align:middle line:10%
that I've been developing.

00:01:12.975 --> 00:01:15.950 align:middle line:10%
It came out of sort of an
inspiration from beyond

00:01:15.950 --> 00:01:18.560 align:middle line:10%
and developed over the years.

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:22.850 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's now considered
to be the leading theory

00:01:22.850 --> 00:01:25.430 align:middle line:10%
to replace physics
in the future.

00:01:25.430 --> 00:01:26.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:27.239 align:middle line:90%
That's dramatic.

00:01:27.239 --> 00:01:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I mean, I don't
know of any other theory that's

00:01:29.780 --> 00:01:35.600 align:middle line:84%
made so many predictions and has
so much interest among people

00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:37.640 align:middle line:84%
who are interested in
alternative theories.

00:01:37.640 --> 00:01:39.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Explain to
we non-physicists

00:01:39.410 --> 00:01:41.150 align:middle line:90%
what sub-quantum kinetics is.

00:01:41.150 --> 00:01:43.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well, meaning
below the quantum level.

00:01:43.880 --> 00:01:48.710 align:middle line:84%
It postulates an ether,
which is an ancient concept.

00:01:48.710 --> 00:01:51.710 align:middle line:84%
And they used to believe
in it 100 years ago

00:01:51.710 --> 00:01:53.780 align:middle line:84%
till they went to
special relativity

00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:56.600 align:middle line:84%
and claimed that
there was no ether.

00:01:56.600 --> 00:02:00.410 align:middle line:84%
But so many experiments
have proven there is.

00:02:00.410 --> 00:02:03.900 align:middle line:84%
At least 10 of them, I
think, I cite in my book.

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:07.424 align:middle line:84%
And there was one recent,
the Grusenick experiment.

00:02:07.424 --> 00:02:08.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is that?

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:10.673 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It's like the
Michelson-Morley experiment,

00:02:10.673 --> 00:02:12.450 align:middle line:84%
where they used
an interferometer

00:02:12.450 --> 00:02:14.930 align:middle line:90%
to look for an ether wind.

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:18.390 align:middle line:84%
It was a key experiment
they did 100 years ago

00:02:18.390 --> 00:02:21.120 align:middle line:84%
to look for the ether,
if there was an ether.

00:02:21.120 --> 00:02:22.750 align:middle line:90%
And they didn't see any result.

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:23.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:02:23.550 --> 00:02:24.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: And that's why--

00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:25.353 align:middle line:90%
they didn't find it.

00:02:25.353 --> 00:02:28.020 align:middle line:84%
So they figured, well,
there is no ether maybe.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:30.750 align:middle line:84%
But then Grusenick,
all he did was

00:02:30.750 --> 00:02:34.980 align:middle line:84%
rotate the interferometer
90 degrees to the vertical.

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:36.450 align:middle line:84%
And there he found
the ether wind.

00:02:36.450 --> 00:02:38.100 align:middle line:84%
It was coming down
into the earth.

00:02:38.100 --> 00:02:39.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is the ether wind?

00:02:39.870 --> 00:02:42.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well, according
to sub-quantum kinetics,

00:02:42.570 --> 00:02:44.400 align:middle line:90%
it's geons.

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.620 align:middle line:84%
I call them geons
going into Earth.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:49.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's what creates a
gravity field of the Earth,

00:02:49.530 --> 00:02:52.740 align:middle line:84%
because they are being
consumed and transformed

00:02:52.740 --> 00:02:57.510 align:middle line:84%
into other types of
sub-quantum particles.

00:02:57.510 --> 00:02:58.580 align:middle line:90%
Think of quarks.

00:02:58.580 --> 00:03:02.310 align:middle line:90%
This is below the quantum level.

00:03:02.310 --> 00:03:05.820 align:middle line:84%
So because there's
a deficit of geons,

00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:07.410 align:middle line:90%
they're flowing into the Earth.

00:03:07.410 --> 00:03:11.580 align:middle line:84%
And it creates a gradient,
a field sort of sloping down

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:12.480 align:middle line:90%
towards the earth.

00:03:12.480 --> 00:03:15.930 align:middle line:84%
And that G gradient,
that ether gradient

00:03:15.930 --> 00:03:18.360 align:middle line:84%
is what creates a
gravitational force.

00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:21.690 align:middle line:84%
And we've simulated this
with computer simulations.

00:03:21.690 --> 00:03:25.890 align:middle line:84%
The equations that sub-quantum
kinetics is proposing,

00:03:25.890 --> 00:03:27.520 align:middle line:90%
we've simulated in the computer.

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:30.450 align:middle line:84%
And we've shown particle-like
structures are affected

00:03:30.450 --> 00:03:32.439 align:middle line:84%
by the field gradients
and actually move,

00:03:32.439 --> 00:03:33.480 align:middle line:90%
just like we were saying.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:36.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Paul, without
gravity, if it didn't exist,

00:03:36.870 --> 00:03:38.670 align:middle line:90%
what would happen, chaos?

00:03:38.670 --> 00:03:41.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well you
wouldn't get the stars forming

00:03:41.820 --> 00:03:43.270 align:middle line:90%
or planets forming.

00:03:43.270 --> 00:03:44.740 align:middle line:84%
The things wouldn't
keep together.

00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:45.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We wouldn't
even be here.

00:03:45.840 --> 00:03:47.506 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It'd
just be dust floating

00:03:47.506 --> 00:03:49.290 align:middle line:90%
in the air without gravity.

00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:52.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, the fact that
it exists tells you what?

00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:55.860 align:middle line:84%
Because the model of the
universe seems to have so much

00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:57.610 align:middle line:90%
order to it.

00:03:57.610 --> 00:04:01.230 align:middle line:84%
Everything seems to fit
like pieces of a puzzle.

00:04:01.230 --> 00:04:03.480 align:middle line:90%
To me, that's remarkable.

00:04:03.480 --> 00:04:07.180 align:middle line:84%
One would say, there's
a creator behind this.

00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:12.420 align:middle line:84%
How do you explain how all of
it works and it works so well?

00:04:12.420 --> 00:04:16.079 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well, I
would differ on that.

00:04:16.079 --> 00:04:19.140 align:middle line:84%
What they do is they
ignore the difficulties

00:04:19.140 --> 00:04:22.230 align:middle line:90%
where there's contradictions.

00:04:22.230 --> 00:04:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And they block any efforts to
disprove the existing theories.

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.620 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult
to publish something

00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:35.570 align:middle line:84%
that is new, that shows
that old theories are wrong.

00:04:35.570 --> 00:04:36.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure does.

00:04:36.370 --> 00:04:40.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: So
physics-- there's

00:04:40.400 --> 00:04:43.970 align:middle line:84%
a whole lot of things
I would throw out.

00:04:43.970 --> 00:04:47.570 align:middle line:84%
And when I say throw it out,
I mean I found the errors.

00:04:47.570 --> 00:04:49.390 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not just giving opinion.

00:04:49.390 --> 00:04:50.930 align:middle line:90%
I found the flaws.

00:04:50.930 --> 00:04:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And it should be thrown
out, like black hole

00:04:53.390 --> 00:04:57.290 align:middle line:84%
theory, special relativity,
general relativity,

00:04:57.290 --> 00:04:58.580 align:middle line:90%
quantum mechanics.

00:04:58.580 --> 00:05:00.492 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would Einstein
and Hawking go crazy?

00:05:00.492 --> 00:05:01.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Probably.

00:05:01.450 --> 00:05:04.190 align:middle line:90%


00:05:04.190 --> 00:05:07.900 align:middle line:84%
And so many other things,
the wave-particle dualism,

00:05:07.900 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
a whole list of things I
would keep classical physics

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:16.065 align:middle line:84%
like Newton's theories of
electrostatics and gravitation,

00:05:16.065 --> 00:05:16.865 align:middle line:90%
Maxwell's theories.

00:05:16.865 --> 00:05:19.560 align:middle line:90%


00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:25.140 align:middle line:84%
But the more advanced physics,
modern physics is wrong.

00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:28.180 align:middle line:84%
And in my book, I
explain the problems.

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:32.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Townsend Brown
is an aerospace engineer.

00:05:32.020 --> 00:05:35.750 align:middle line:84%
And he talks about the
tie-in between electricity

00:05:35.750 --> 00:05:36.800 align:middle line:90%
and gravity.

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:40.430 align:middle line:10%
>> In the 1950s, as waves
of flying saucer sightings

00:05:40.430 --> 00:05:42.920 align:middle line:10%
occurred throughout the United
States and while an infant

00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:45.320 align:middle line:10%
space program was
trying to catch up with

00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:48.380 align:middle line:10%
the Russians' launch of
Sputnik, a man named T.

00:05:48.380 --> 00:05:52.490 align:middle line:84%
Townsend Brown was busy
on experiments that defied

00:05:52.490 --> 00:05:56.000 align:middle line:84%
conventional understanding
of electricity, gravitation,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:57.170 align:middle line:90%
and propulsion.

00:05:57.170 --> 00:06:01.130 align:middle line:84%
Along with doctors Paul
Bifield and Agnew Bunsen,

00:06:01.130 --> 00:06:03.365 align:middle line:84%
Brown took high voltage
to the next extreme.

00:06:03.365 --> 00:06:06.410 align:middle line:90%


00:06:06.410 --> 00:06:09.840 align:middle line:84%
In this rare home movie,
the earliest experiments

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:11.390 align:middle line:84%
in electrogravitics
are recorded.

00:06:11.390 --> 00:06:13.608 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:13.608 --> 00:06:30.158 align:middle line:90%


00:06:30.158 --> 00:06:35.180 align:middle line:84%
By using high voltages, over
20,000 and up to 200,000 volts,

00:06:35.180 --> 00:06:37.970 align:middle line:84%
Brown discovered that
highly charged capacitors

00:06:37.970 --> 00:06:41.230 align:middle line:84%
would exhibit a noticeable
thrust in one direction.

00:06:41.230 --> 00:06:46.190 align:middle line:90%


00:06:46.190 --> 00:06:50.040 align:middle line:84%
Although awarded a patent for
his electrokinetic generator,

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:55.520 align:middle line:84%
no one has ever reproduced
his experiment until recently.

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:57.710 align:middle line:84%
Larry Davenport, shown
here demonstrating

00:06:57.710 --> 00:07:00.165 align:middle line:84%
his replication of Brown's
electrokinetic apparatus

00:07:00.165 --> 00:07:00.965 align:middle line:90%
explains.

00:07:00.965 --> 00:07:03.311 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.311 --> 00:07:05.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LARRY DAVENPORT: When I first
began to read Brown's stuff,

00:07:05.810 --> 00:07:10.580 align:middle line:84%
I didn't quite understand the
difference between the ion wind

00:07:10.580 --> 00:07:12.650 align:middle line:84%
devices, which there's a
lot of them out there--

00:07:12.650 --> 00:07:15.410 align:middle line:84%
and some of them are very
efficient as far as producing

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:17.270 align:middle line:90%
ion wind--

00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.290 align:middle line:90%
and his particular apparatus.

00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:24.590 align:middle line:84%
I finally decided to do
Brown's work in 1994.

00:07:24.590 --> 00:07:26.152 align:middle line:10%
I looked at his device.

00:07:26.152 --> 00:07:28.610 align:middle line:10%
I'd tried several different
things, and they hadn't worked.

00:07:28.610 --> 00:07:30.260 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
Brown is supposed

00:07:30.260 --> 00:07:34.580 align:middle line:84%
to be the pioneer of this, or
the people that make the claims

00:07:34.580 --> 00:07:38.420 align:middle line:84%
and that get the patents,
they always refer to his name.

00:07:38.420 --> 00:07:40.730 align:middle line:84%
So I thought I'd go back
and I'll try to do this.

00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:43.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How far ahead of
time was Townsend Brown?

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:45.469 align:middle line:90%
Was he way ahead of his time?

00:07:45.469 --> 00:07:47.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: He was
further than Einstein.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:48.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:07:48.060 --> 00:07:49.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Oh, yeah.

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:51.580 align:middle line:84%
In fact, Einstein
and Brown, I believe,

00:07:51.580 --> 00:07:57.880 align:middle line:84%
were working together, uh,
black project during the war

00:07:57.880 --> 00:07:59.974 align:middle line:84%
called the Philadelphia
Experiment.

00:07:59.974 --> 00:08:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But there's much
more to that, isn't there?

00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:05.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Where they made a
ship disappear, not only radar

00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:08.920 align:middle line:84%
invisible but actually optical
invisible, it's claimed.

00:08:08.920 --> 00:08:14.330 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that Einstein
knew about Brown's work,

00:08:14.330 --> 00:08:17.830 align:middle line:84%
because Brown had done his
work on electrogravitics.

00:08:17.830 --> 00:08:20.800 align:middle line:84%
Already in '20s he
knew about this.

00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.830 align:middle line:84%
And after that, we
remember Einstein

00:08:23.830 --> 00:08:26.560 align:middle line:84%
trying to find a unification
between electricity

00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:28.870 align:middle line:84%
and gravitation, which
Brown had already

00:08:28.870 --> 00:08:32.140 align:middle line:84%
shown there was a
unification, that electricity

00:08:32.140 --> 00:08:33.789 align:middle line:90%
is affecting gravity.

00:08:33.789 --> 00:08:37.750 align:middle line:84%
And that's what electrogravitics
is, electricity effect

00:08:37.750 --> 00:08:38.590 align:middle line:90%
affecting gravity.

00:08:38.590 --> 00:08:39.965 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Where
would you have put

00:08:39.965 --> 00:08:42.685 align:middle line:84%
Tesla in the middle of
this at the time Tesla?

00:08:42.685 --> 00:08:46.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Tesla, they say,
was part of the project also.

00:08:46.270 --> 00:08:49.555 align:middle line:84%
I discuss the Philadelphia
project in my book,

00:08:49.555 --> 00:08:51.730 align:middle line:84%
in "Secrets of
Anti-Gravity Propulsion."

00:08:51.730 --> 00:08:55.300 align:middle line:84%
Some of the work of Tesla
was applicable to this,

00:08:55.300 --> 00:08:57.910 align:middle line:84%
because they were using
pulses, I believe,

00:08:57.910 --> 00:08:59.887 align:middle line:90%
to create this effect.

00:08:59.887 --> 00:09:02.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you bring up the
Philadelphia Experiment, Paul.

00:09:02.470 --> 00:09:05.500 align:middle line:84%
And I have had guests
on "Coast to Coast"

00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:10.450 align:middle line:84%
over the years, a fellow by
the name of Al Bielek, Duncan

00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:14.500 align:middle line:84%
Cameron, who claimed that they
were part of the experiment.

00:09:14.500 --> 00:09:15.700 align:middle line:90%
And this is what they say.

00:09:15.700 --> 00:09:17.840 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to get
your reaction to it.

00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:19.990 align:middle line:84%
They say that
something went awry

00:09:19.990 --> 00:09:24.760 align:middle line:84%
with trying to cloak the ship
in the Philadelphia shipyard

00:09:24.760 --> 00:09:29.830 align:middle line:84%
and that it literally made
the soldiers and the Navy

00:09:29.830 --> 00:09:34.870 align:middle line:84%
people on the ship
disappear, or in some cases,

00:09:34.870 --> 00:09:38.569 align:middle line:84%
half of their body was in our
plane, the other half was gone.

00:09:38.569 --> 00:09:39.610 align:middle line:90%
Do you think that's true?

00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:40.540 align:middle line:90%
Was that real?

00:09:40.540 --> 00:09:42.164 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yes,
I believe, because--

00:09:42.164 --> 00:09:42.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: My god!

00:09:42.970 --> 00:09:44.386 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I
can understand how

00:09:44.386 --> 00:09:47.590 align:middle line:84%
that happened in the context
of sub-quantum kinetics.

00:09:47.590 --> 00:09:49.190 align:middle line:84%
In physics, it's
a total mystery,

00:09:49.190 --> 00:09:51.010 align:middle line:90%
and nobody believes it.

00:09:51.010 --> 00:09:52.720 align:middle line:84%
But in sub-quantum
kinetics, if you

00:09:52.720 --> 00:09:59.540 align:middle line:84%
can change the gravity potential
by pulsing with electric pulses

00:09:59.540 --> 00:10:05.180 align:middle line:84%
and raise the potential--
so we're in a gravity well.

00:10:05.180 --> 00:10:08.000 align:middle line:84%
If you can create
a gravity hill,

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:11.030 align:middle line:84%
things will disappear optically,
because what will happen

00:10:11.030 --> 00:10:16.010 align:middle line:84%
is, the subatomic particle has
a wave pattern around it that

00:10:16.010 --> 00:10:17.360 align:middle line:90%
stops light from going through.

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:19.670 align:middle line:84%
That's why light doesn't
go through solid matter,

00:10:19.670 --> 00:10:21.050 align:middle line:90%
except maybe glass.

00:10:21.050 --> 00:10:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Those would disappear
first before the cores

00:10:24.600 --> 00:10:25.400 align:middle line:90%
would disappear.

00:10:25.400 --> 00:10:26.990 align:middle line:84%
So the particles
would still be there.

00:10:26.990 --> 00:10:29.270 align:middle line:84%
But now light could
actually go through.

00:10:29.270 --> 00:10:31.220 align:middle line:84%
And it would look
like it's invisible.

00:10:31.220 --> 00:10:34.840 align:middle line:84%
And also people
could blend with--

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:37.130 align:middle line:90%
put your arm through.

00:10:37.130 --> 00:10:40.670 align:middle line:84%
But then you put the
gravity potential

00:10:40.670 --> 00:10:43.820 align:middle line:84%
back down to create
normal gravity,

00:10:43.820 --> 00:10:45.560 align:middle line:90%
and everything will come back.

00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:49.820 align:middle line:84%
And if you had your arm in
a wall, you're stuck there.

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:50.780 align:middle line:90%
You can't get out.

00:10:50.780 --> 00:10:50.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whoa.

00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:52.126 align:middle line:90%
So this might have happened.

00:10:52.126 --> 00:10:54.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I believe it did.

00:10:54.610 --> 00:10:57.790 align:middle line:84%
And I believe, because of
that, they kept it so secret.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:11:02.620 align:middle line:84%
They even changed--
the Navy changed

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:05.410 align:middle line:84%
Brown's date of
departure from the Navy

00:11:05.410 --> 00:11:08.590 align:middle line:84%
so it looked like he left before
the Philadelphia Experiment.

00:11:08.590 --> 00:11:10.340 align:middle line:90%
They were trying to--

00:11:10.340 --> 00:11:11.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Mask it.

00:11:11.140 --> 00:11:12.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Mask him, yeah.

00:11:12.580 --> 00:11:14.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
Project Winterhaven?

00:11:14.830 --> 00:11:18.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: That was a project
that Brown proposed to the Navy

00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:22.690 align:middle line:84%
to develop a disk craft
that would have Mach 3

00:11:22.690 --> 00:11:26.090 align:middle line:84%
capabilities, which was faster
than anything they had back

00:11:26.090 --> 00:11:26.890 align:middle line:90%
then.

00:11:26.890 --> 00:11:28.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Like flying saucers?

00:11:28.510 --> 00:11:29.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:11:29.860 --> 00:11:34.560 align:middle line:84%
Using his electrogravitics,
electrokinetics technology.

00:11:34.560 --> 00:11:41.250 align:middle line:84%
And in the report, it's an
interesting thing in there.

00:11:41.250 --> 00:11:47.340 align:middle line:84%
Brown is saying that he had
been prevented from discussing

00:11:47.340 --> 00:11:50.010 align:middle line:90%
his work in publications.

00:11:50.010 --> 00:11:52.211 align:middle line:84%
So here's Einstein
publishing freely.

00:11:52.211 --> 00:11:53.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, like crazy, yeah.

00:11:53.460 --> 00:11:56.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: And Brown
isn't allowed to publish.

00:11:56.490 --> 00:12:00.465 align:middle line:84%
In fact, after '59, the
whole field went dark.

00:12:00.465 --> 00:12:03.870 align:middle line:90%


00:12:03.870 --> 00:12:06.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, the aircraft
industry was not

00:12:06.210 --> 00:12:09.240 align:middle line:84%
allowed to speak to
the media any longer

00:12:09.240 --> 00:12:11.940 align:middle line:84%
about the research
they were doing.

00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:14.070 align:middle line:90%
And none of us knew about this.

00:12:14.070 --> 00:12:17.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was known
back in the early '50s

00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:20.230 align:middle line:84%
that there was electrogravitics
research going on.

00:12:20.230 --> 00:12:22.110 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't secret.

00:12:22.110 --> 00:12:26.880 align:middle line:84%
It was in magazines like
"Product Engineering."

00:12:26.880 --> 00:12:28.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: "Popular Mechanics?"

00:12:28.620 --> 00:12:30.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Things like that.

00:12:30.180 --> 00:12:33.590 align:middle line:84%
And then people forgot
about it, because it

00:12:33.590 --> 00:12:34.640 align:middle line:90%
wasn't discussed anymore.

00:12:34.640 --> 00:12:35.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:12:35.510 --> 00:12:36.950 align:middle line:90%
Out of sight, out of mind.

00:12:36.950 --> 00:12:37.783 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Right.

00:12:37.783 --> 00:12:41.309 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think those
projects are continuing today?

00:12:41.309 --> 00:12:42.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Definitely.

00:12:42.350 --> 00:12:45.870 align:middle line:84%
For example, Brown's
technology, this disk proposal,

00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:50.065 align:middle line:84%
the Winterhaven proposal ended
up turning into the B2 bomber.

00:12:50.065 --> 00:12:51.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Since
you bring that up,

00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:54.860 align:middle line:90%
let's look at the B2 bomber.

00:12:54.860 --> 00:12:58.010 align:middle line:10%
>> In the history of aviation,
there has never been a plane

00:12:58.010 --> 00:13:02.900 align:middle line:10%
more groundbreaking than
the B2 stealth bomber.

00:13:02.900 --> 00:13:06.380 align:middle line:84%
Capable of flying anywhere
in the world undetected,

00:13:06.380 --> 00:13:08.880 align:middle line:84%
the B2 can arrive
over its target,

00:13:08.880 --> 00:13:12.890 align:middle line:84%
release precision munitions,
and escape confident in the fact

00:13:12.890 --> 00:13:15.200 align:middle line:84%
that the bombs will
hit their targets

00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:18.560 align:middle line:84%
and that the plane will
return home safely.

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:22.310 align:middle line:84%
Revolutionary in design
and capability, the B2

00:13:22.310 --> 00:13:26.090 align:middle line:84%
represents the culmination of
many disciplines and sciences,

00:13:26.090 --> 00:13:30.090 align:middle line:84%
from aeronautics to
stealth to bombing itself.

00:13:30.090 --> 00:13:32.420 align:middle line:84%
It also has a
distinction unshared

00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:34.700 align:middle line:90%
by any conventional aircraft.

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:37.100 align:middle line:84%
For the entirety of
its service life,

00:13:37.100 --> 00:13:42.320 align:middle line:84%
the B2 has never been
detected, targeted, or engaged.

00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:45.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is that still
an action, the B2 bomber?

00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:46.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Oh, yeah.

00:13:46.560 --> 00:13:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I bet they've
perfected it even more.

00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:51.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I
wouldn't be surprised.

00:13:51.220 --> 00:13:53.550 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if they call
it the B2 any longer.

00:13:53.550 --> 00:13:56.337 align:middle line:84%
The perfected version might
be named something else.

00:13:56.337 --> 00:13:57.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good point.

00:13:57.170 --> 00:13:58.470 align:middle line:10%
>>LAVIOLETTE: They
don't' talk about it.

00:13:58.470 --> 00:14:00.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: God, the
technology that we

00:14:00.050 --> 00:14:03.240 align:middle line:84%
possess, Paul, is beyond
what anybody would imagine,

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:04.040 align:middle line:90%
isn't that?

00:14:04.040 --> 00:14:04.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:05.480 align:middle line:90%
Here, we're using it.

00:14:05.480 --> 00:14:07.400 align:middle line:90%
We acknowledge the B2.

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:10.840 align:middle line:84%
But the propulsion
system is secret.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:12.950 align:middle line:84%
And they even say
that the secret thing

00:14:12.950 --> 00:14:14.810 align:middle line:90%
is the radar invisibility.

00:14:14.810 --> 00:14:18.390 align:middle line:84%
But that's to get you away from
thinking about the propulsion

00:14:18.390 --> 00:14:19.190 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:14:19.190 --> 00:14:20.570 align:middle line:84%
It's really the
propulsion system

00:14:20.570 --> 00:14:22.994 align:middle line:90%
that's so highly classified.

00:14:22.994 --> 00:14:25.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think
the propulsion system is?

00:14:25.160 --> 00:14:28.250 align:middle line:10%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It was leaked by
some black project scientists

00:14:28.250 --> 00:14:31.580 align:middle line:10%
and published in "Aviation
Week" and "Space Technology"

00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:36.230 align:middle line:10%
back around '92 that the
B2 charges the leading edge

00:14:36.230 --> 00:14:38.810 align:middle line:10%
of its wing to high voltage.

00:14:38.810 --> 00:14:41.940 align:middle line:84%
And the opposite charge
they dump in the exhaust.

00:14:41.940 --> 00:14:45.050 align:middle line:84%
And so they're creating
this huge field gradient

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:46.070 align:middle line:90%
across the craft.

00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:48.350 align:middle line:84%
So that was the main
thing they leaked.

00:14:48.350 --> 00:14:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And based on that, and knowing
Brown's patents that he

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:53.510 align:middle line:90%
published back in the '50s--

00:14:53.510 --> 00:14:54.860 align:middle line:90%
and he was proposing this.

00:14:54.860 --> 00:14:58.010 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't suppressed at all.

00:14:58.010 --> 00:15:00.830 align:middle line:90%
It was exactly the idea.

00:15:00.830 --> 00:15:03.260 align:middle line:10%
He showed charging the
leading edge of the craft

00:15:03.260 --> 00:15:05.090 align:middle line:10%
and using a flame
jet generator-- that

00:15:05.090 --> 00:15:07.700 align:middle line:10%
was the other thing that the
fellow mentioned, that they

00:15:07.700 --> 00:15:11.000 align:middle line:10%
generate the high voltage
difference in the jet engine

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:13.920 align:middle line:10%
itself using a
flame jet generator.

00:15:13.920 --> 00:15:15.455 align:middle line:90%
Townsend Brown developed that.

00:15:15.455 --> 00:15:15.830 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Amazing.

00:15:15.830 --> 00:15:17.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: He was the
guy who developed that.

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How far ahead are
we from the other countries,

00:15:19.700 --> 00:15:22.820 align:middle line:84%
China, Russia, with
this kind of technology?

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:24.170 align:middle line:90%
Or have they caught up with us?

00:15:24.170 --> 00:15:27.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I think China has
bases in space, just like we do

00:15:27.560 --> 00:15:29.120 align:middle line:90%
and the Russians do.

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:32.520 align:middle line:84%
And they're developing
advanced propulsion.

00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:34.854 align:middle line:84%
It's just, they're very
good at keeping secrets.

00:15:34.854 --> 00:15:36.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Better than we are?

00:15:36.020 --> 00:15:37.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Right.

00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:41.090 align:middle line:84%
They have a law now that
if anybody falsifies

00:15:41.090 --> 00:15:44.630 align:middle line:84%
scientific data, they have the
death sentence for that person.

00:15:44.630 --> 00:15:46.070 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: God.

00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:48.130 align:middle line:84%
And here, what would
happen in the United States

00:15:48.130 --> 00:15:48.930 align:middle line:90%
for that, nothing?

00:15:48.930 --> 00:15:50.150 align:middle line:90%
Probably a hand slap?

00:15:50.150 --> 00:15:52.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Maybe
embarrassed by a publication.

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:53.640 align:middle line:90%
That's about it.

00:15:53.640 --> 00:15:55.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Paul, when
you talk about bases,

00:15:55.670 --> 00:15:57.530 align:middle line:90%
where might they be?

00:15:57.530 --> 00:15:59.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well, I
believe outside Earth orbit

00:15:59.840 --> 00:16:02.675 align:middle line:90%
there are bases.

00:16:02.675 --> 00:16:05.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Like space stations
or on the moon or something

00:16:05.010 --> 00:16:05.810 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:16:05.810 --> 00:16:12.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It could be bases
on planets, like Mars, Ceres.

00:16:12.190 --> 00:16:16.270 align:middle line:84%
We sent a probe out to
Ceres a few years ago.

00:16:16.270 --> 00:16:19.120 align:middle line:84%
And they were shooting
back pictures.

00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:22.150 align:middle line:84%
And you saw what looked
like white areas that

00:16:22.150 --> 00:16:25.520 align:middle line:84%
looked just like they could
have been cities down there.

00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:26.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, reflected.

00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:29.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: And I published
about this on the internet.

00:16:29.500 --> 00:16:32.650 align:middle line:84%
And I show pictures that we've
taken of Ceres from the air,

00:16:32.650 --> 00:16:34.360 align:middle line:84%
from satellites, from
the space station

00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:36.760 align:middle line:84%
and compare with what
they're seeing there.

00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:38.830 align:middle line:84%
And a very, very
close resemblance.

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:41.092 align:middle line:84%
Now, why is it that when
they got very close,

00:16:41.092 --> 00:16:42.550 align:middle line:84%
they didn't send
any more pictures?

00:16:42.550 --> 00:16:43.466 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They stopped.

00:16:43.466 --> 00:16:44.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Right.

00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:46.460 align:middle line:84%
Right when we were hoping
we'd get close enough

00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:47.260 align:middle line:90%
to see something.

00:16:47.260 --> 00:16:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And then they didn't
send anything more.

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:51.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Possibilities of this
then you think are very high?

00:16:51.130 --> 00:16:52.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: From
what I know and a lot

00:16:52.900 --> 00:16:56.050 align:middle line:84%
of things which we probably
won't have time to discuss,

00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:57.430 align:middle line:90%
I am very certain.

00:16:57.430 --> 00:17:01.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What about
continuing to send astronauts

00:17:01.330 --> 00:17:03.490 align:middle line:90%
and flying them into space?

00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:07.810 align:middle line:84%
We think that since we stopped
the space shuttle program,

00:17:07.810 --> 00:17:09.589 align:middle line:90%
we've stopped all of that.

00:17:09.589 --> 00:17:11.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm not so sure we have.

00:17:11.130 --> 00:17:14.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: No We
continue to travel.

00:17:14.740 --> 00:17:19.390 align:middle line:84%
There's regular
sightings near Area 51.

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.510 align:middle line:84%
Even out in the Los
Angeles area people

00:17:22.510 --> 00:17:25.180 align:middle line:90%
have seen UFOs, secret bases.

00:17:25.180 --> 00:17:28.960 align:middle line:84%
I heard a story from a friend
of mine that he was hang gliding

00:17:28.960 --> 00:17:30.690 align:middle line:84%
or his friends
were hang gliding.

00:17:30.690 --> 00:17:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And they had to come down
in a mountainous area

00:17:32.890 --> 00:17:37.600 align:middle line:84%
between the shore and some
mountains right north of LA.

00:17:37.600 --> 00:17:41.170 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't way out in nowhere.

00:17:41.170 --> 00:17:43.180 align:middle line:84%
And there was a landing
strip they found.

00:17:43.180 --> 00:17:44.650 align:middle line:84%
Because they were
losing altitude,

00:17:44.650 --> 00:17:46.483 align:middle line:84%
they had to land somewhere
in the mountains.

00:17:46.483 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:90%
And they found a landing strip.

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:48.670 align:middle line:90%
They get down.

00:17:48.670 --> 00:17:51.730 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, they're surrounded
with people with guns.

00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:52.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:17:52.600 --> 00:17:54.225 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: At the
end of the landing

00:17:54.225 --> 00:17:59.830 align:middle line:84%
strip was a disk
hovering inside a tent.

00:17:59.830 --> 00:18:02.550 align:middle line:84%
And they were told they're not
supposed to say this to anyone.

00:18:02.550 --> 00:18:10.640 align:middle line:84%
So this is obviously one
of ours, it seems to me.

00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:12.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's not E.T.

00:18:12.110 --> 00:18:13.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:18:13.210 --> 00:18:15.650 align:middle line:84%
A chance encounter,
and they see a disk.

00:18:15.650 --> 00:18:16.800 align:middle line:90%
What's the chance of that?

00:18:16.800 --> 00:18:17.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What are the odds?

00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:18.320 align:middle line:90%
What are the odds?

00:18:18.320 --> 00:18:20.390 align:middle line:84%
They say it takes
us up to six months

00:18:20.390 --> 00:18:23.534 align:middle line:84%
to travel from Earth to Mars
on any given time period.

00:18:23.534 --> 00:18:24.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I
think nine months.

00:18:24.950 --> 00:18:26.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or nine months as well.

00:18:26.430 --> 00:18:28.820 align:middle line:84%
But through Townsend's
work, could we

00:18:28.820 --> 00:18:30.360 align:middle line:90%
have gotten there quicker?

00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yes.

00:18:31.160 --> 00:18:34.370 align:middle line:84%
In my book, I talk about
going to Mars in five days.

00:18:34.370 --> 00:18:35.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Five days?

00:18:35.510 --> 00:18:36.926 align:middle line:10%
>>LAVIOLETTE: We
could go quicker.

00:18:36.926 --> 00:18:39.339 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to make it
sound too unbelievable.

00:18:39.339 --> 00:18:41.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Five days is
kind of unbelievable.

00:18:41.130 --> 00:18:43.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Using
Townsend Brown's thrusters,

00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:45.420 align:middle line:90%
his electrokinetic thrusters.

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:46.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whoa!

00:18:46.760 --> 00:18:48.860 align:middle line:10%
>>LAVIOLETTE: His
umbrella-like device, it

00:18:48.860 --> 00:18:52.310 align:middle line:10%
has a big positive electrode
and a small negative.

00:18:52.310 --> 00:18:58.480 align:middle line:10%
And he's got a insulator in
between, like barium titanate.

00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:04.930 align:middle line:10%
He's found that these produce
70,000 Newtons per kilowatt.

00:19:04.930 --> 00:19:10.210 align:middle line:84%
That's 5,000 times more thrust
per energy input than a jet

00:19:10.210 --> 00:19:14.350 align:middle line:84%
engine, about 300,000 times
more than a space shuttle

00:19:14.350 --> 00:19:15.370 align:middle line:90%
main engine.

00:19:15.370 --> 00:19:18.400 align:middle line:84%
So it means they're getting,
let's say, 300,000 times

00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:20.710 align:middle line:84%
more thrust for the
amount of energy,

00:19:20.710 --> 00:19:23.950 align:middle line:84%
whether it's chemical energy
or electrical or whatever,

00:19:23.950 --> 00:19:26.515 align:middle line:84%
than we get with our
commercial versions.

00:19:26.515 --> 00:19:29.610 align:middle line:90%


00:19:29.610 --> 00:19:33.840 align:middle line:84%
So with this and an
array of thrusters,

00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:36.550 align:middle line:84%
you can picture a ship,
about like the space shuttle,

00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:41.280 align:middle line:84%
100-ton craft, with a
series of these thrusters,

