and invented free energy.

00:26:09.090 --> 00:26:12.120 align:middle line:10%
>> In the 19th century, Tesla
hypothesized that electrical

00:26:12.120 --> 00:26:14.610 align:middle line:10%
power could be generated
using the natural resources

00:26:14.610 --> 00:26:15.960 align:middle line:10%
of the Sun and Earth.

00:26:15.960 --> 00:26:18.150 align:middle line:10%
Tesla understood that by
harnessing the planet's

00:26:18.150 --> 00:26:20.970 align:middle line:10%
natural energy, it could be
provided to the whole world's

00:26:20.970 --> 00:26:22.560 align:middle line:10%
population for free.

00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:24.750 align:middle line:10%
Tesla had already
demonstrated that power

00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:27.630 align:middle line:10%
could be transferred wirelessly
to the American Institute

00:26:27.630 --> 00:26:29.220 align:middle line:10%
of Electrical Engineers.

00:26:29.220 --> 00:26:32.310 align:middle line:84%
Using two metal sheets and
his Tesla coil oscillator,

00:26:32.310 --> 00:26:35.700 align:middle line:84%
he lit up two glass discharge
tubes without wires.

00:26:35.700 --> 00:26:39.060 align:middle line:84%
Now he wanted to implement
the theory on a grand scale.

00:26:39.060 --> 00:26:42.240 align:middle line:84%
In 1901, construction began
on the Wardenclyffe Tower

00:26:42.240 --> 00:26:43.990 align:middle line:90%
in Shoreham, New York.

00:26:43.990 --> 00:26:47.460 align:middle line:84%
Atop the 57-meter tall
tower was a 55-ton dome

00:26:47.460 --> 00:26:48.660 align:middle line:90%
of conductive metal.

00:26:48.660 --> 00:26:52.110 align:middle line:10%
Beneath it, an iron root system
penetrated more than 300 feet

00:26:52.110 --> 00:26:53.490 align:middle line:10%
into the Earth's crust.

00:26:53.490 --> 00:26:56.370 align:middle line:84%
Tesla believed the tower would
harness the Earth's energy

00:26:56.370 --> 00:26:58.350 align:middle line:84%
and transmit it
into the atmosphere.

00:26:58.350 --> 00:27:01.860 align:middle line:84%
Tesla envisaged a global network
of these high-voltage towers

00:27:01.860 --> 00:27:03.630 align:middle line:84%
which would provide
cost-free wireless

00:27:03.630 --> 00:27:05.370 align:middle line:90%
electricity to the masses.

00:27:05.370 --> 00:27:07.246 align:middle line:84%
Homes, businesses,
and even ships

00:27:07.246 --> 00:27:09.120 align:middle line:84%
could draw power from
the electrical currents

00:27:09.120 --> 00:27:10.530 align:middle line:90%
the towers provided.

00:27:10.530 --> 00:27:12.810 align:middle line:84%
The development of wireless
trans-Atlantic telegraphs

00:27:12.810 --> 00:27:16.170 align:middle line:84%
in 1901 and successful
signal testing on the tower

00:27:16.170 --> 00:27:18.960 align:middle line:84%
was promising for the
development of free energy.

00:27:18.960 --> 00:27:21.930 align:middle line:84%
The tower was funded
by J.P. Morgan.

00:27:21.930 --> 00:27:27.830 align:middle line:84%
He gave Tesla $150,000 in return
for 51% control of the patents.

00:27:27.830 --> 00:27:30.510 align:middle line:84%
But to Tesla's shock,
construction on the tower

00:27:30.510 --> 00:27:32.880 align:middle line:90%
was abandoned in 1905.

00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:35.970 align:middle line:84%
J.P. Morgan had
withdrawn his support.

00:27:35.970 --> 00:27:38.460 align:middle line:84%
Why would Morgan back
out just as Tesla

00:27:38.460 --> 00:27:41.460 align:middle line:84%
