00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:33.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:28:33.360 --> 00:28:38.220 align:middle line:84%
This black project scientist
who talked about the B2,

00:28:38.220 --> 00:28:40.360 align:middle line:90%
I had a conversation with him.

00:28:40.360 --> 00:28:45.500 align:middle line:84%
I got his phone number
through the magazine.

00:28:45.500 --> 00:28:50.800 align:middle line:84%
He said that declassified
work in black projects,

00:28:50.800 --> 00:28:54.124 align:middle line:84%
they rely heavily on
Tesla's work and Brown's.

00:28:54.124 --> 00:28:55.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Both of them?

00:28:55.040 --> 00:28:55.915 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Mm-hmm.

00:28:55.915 --> 00:28:58.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Brown must have
been a genius at his time?

00:28:58.660 --> 00:28:59.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yes.

00:28:59.900 --> 00:29:04.370 align:middle line:84%
Brown would have been
the big physics genius

00:29:04.370 --> 00:29:06.411 align:middle line:84%
if he had been allowed
to publish his work

00:29:06.411 --> 00:29:07.660 align:middle line:90%
and if they'd talked about it.

00:29:07.660 --> 00:29:08.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:29:08.010 --> 00:29:09.890 align:middle line:84%
They were pushing
Einstein and not him.

00:29:09.890 --> 00:29:11.931 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Well, they
wanted to push Einstein,

00:29:11.931 --> 00:29:16.490 align:middle line:84%
because with Einstein's theory,
you think that all of this

00:29:16.490 --> 00:29:18.860 align:middle line:84%
is impossible, because
it's not possible.

00:29:18.860 --> 00:29:23.600 align:middle line:84%
He is not able to bend
gravity with electricity.

00:29:23.600 --> 00:29:26.570 align:middle line:84%
Only Brown could create
gravitational force

00:29:26.570 --> 00:29:27.620 align:middle line:90%
with electricity.

00:29:27.620 --> 00:29:30.380 align:middle line:84%
But his theory, he
claimed warping space.

00:29:30.380 --> 00:29:32.297 align:middle line:84%
You can't do it
with electricity.

00:29:32.297 --> 00:29:34.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you had a chance to
talk to Townsend Brown, had he

00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:37.850 align:middle line:84%
been here still, what
would you have asked him?

00:29:37.850 --> 00:29:40.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I suppose
more details on his work.

00:29:40.340 --> 00:29:42.850 align:middle line:90%


00:29:42.850 --> 00:29:46.000 align:middle line:84%
Like, there was one
photocopy of a paper

00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:51.280 align:middle line:84%
from when he was working later
on in the '50s at a company

00:29:51.280 --> 00:29:53.980 align:middle line:84%
that we got a lot of
interesting information

00:29:53.980 --> 00:29:57.990 align:middle line:84%
about his experiments, lifting
devices off the ground.

00:29:57.990 --> 00:30:01.810 align:middle line:84%
And there must be so
much more that they don't

00:30:01.810 --> 00:30:04.190 align:middle line:90%
allow to go out that Brown did.

00:30:04.190 --> 00:30:07.000 align:middle line:84%
But I would have asked
him more about his work.

00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:09.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Could these
applications of propulsion,

00:30:09.040 --> 00:30:11.270 align:middle line:90%
Paul, be used for airlines?

00:30:11.270 --> 00:30:12.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yes.

00:30:12.070 --> 00:30:14.800 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can we one day
be flying from Los Angeles

00:30:14.800 --> 00:30:17.320 align:middle line:90%
to New York in 30 minutes?

00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:19.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Right, you could.

00:30:19.330 --> 00:30:23.710 align:middle line:84%
Not only would the B2
bomber propulsion systems,

00:30:23.710 --> 00:30:28.270 align:middle line:84%
similar to the B2 bomber
create a driving force

00:30:28.270 --> 00:30:31.970 align:middle line:84%
that could go many times
the speed of sound,

00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:35.586 align:middle line:84%
but it reduces the air
drag, because in the front,

00:30:35.586 --> 00:30:37.460 align:middle line:84%
you're charging the
leading edge of the wing.

00:30:37.460 --> 00:30:40.060 align:middle line:84%
So it repels the
air from the craft.

00:30:40.060 --> 00:30:42.910 align:middle line:84%
So the air sort of
slides around it.

00:30:42.910 --> 00:30:44.710 align:middle line:84%
And it sort of slips
through the air

00:30:44.710 --> 00:30:46.877 align:middle line:90%
with very little resistance.

00:30:46.877 --> 00:30:48.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, that
would be dramatic.

00:30:48.460 --> 00:30:49.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:30:49.450 --> 00:30:50.470 align:middle line:90%
What a great flight.

00:30:50.470 --> 00:30:52.660 align:middle line:84%
You could cut,
dramatically, fuel bills.

00:30:52.660 --> 00:30:58.260 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you ran
it on gasoline.

00:30:58.260 --> 00:31:02.200 align:middle line:84%
You could probably do it
on 10% of what you use now.

00:31:02.200 --> 00:31:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And that's a big
cost in air travel.

00:31:04.260 --> 00:31:06.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How about cars?

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:07.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah,
you could add this.

00:31:07.860 --> 00:31:08.660 align:middle line:90%
I know one guy.

00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:10.350 align:middle line:84%
He's thinking of
entering a race.

00:31:10.350 --> 00:31:11.867 align:middle line:90%
He put it on a car.

00:31:11.867 --> 00:31:13.200 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That would be exciting.

00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:15.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: You could
really break the records.

00:31:15.570 --> 00:31:17.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Instantly.

00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:19.470 align:middle line:84%
The salt flats would
look like nothing.

00:31:19.470 --> 00:31:22.110 align:middle line:84%
Paul, tell us about
Eugene Podkletnov.

00:31:22.110 --> 00:31:24.780 align:middle line:90%
He investigated gravity?

00:31:24.780 --> 00:31:25.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:31:25.580 --> 00:31:27.750 align:middle line:90%
He had sort of like a laser.

00:31:27.750 --> 00:31:31.620 align:middle line:10%
But he'd send a
pulse down through

00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:36.750 align:middle line:10%
a superconducting
piece, a cylinder.

00:31:36.750 --> 00:31:39.630 align:middle line:84%
And it would create a
wave, an electric charge

00:31:39.630 --> 00:31:44.416 align:middle line:84%
wave that would go down and
hit an electrode, an anode.

00:31:44.416 --> 00:31:48.020 align:middle line:84%
And then he found that even
though the electrons stopped,

00:31:48.020 --> 00:31:49.480 align:middle line:90%
the gravity wave continued.

00:31:49.480 --> 00:31:50.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Uh-huh.

00:31:50.280 --> 00:31:53.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: And it was
collimated just like a laser,

00:31:53.950 --> 00:31:55.970 align:middle line:84%
because he had
magnetic confinement.

00:31:55.970 --> 00:31:58.370 align:middle line:90%
So it sort of confined it.

00:31:58.370 --> 00:32:02.080 align:middle line:84%
And he actually would
knock over books

00:32:02.080 --> 00:32:03.260 align:middle line:90%
at two miles away with this.

00:32:03.260 --> 00:32:04.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:32:04.060 --> 00:32:04.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah.

00:32:04.900 --> 00:32:06.700 align:middle line:90%
And that was his low-power unit.

00:32:06.700 --> 00:32:09.400 align:middle line:84%
Then he developed a
higher-power unit which is now

00:32:09.400 --> 00:32:12.280 align:middle line:90%
in a secure facility in Moscow.

00:32:12.280 --> 00:32:15.880 align:middle line:84%
And with that, they put a 4-inch
hole through a concrete block

00:32:15.880 --> 00:32:19.070 align:middle line:84%
and was able to dent a
1-inch thick steel plate.

00:32:19.070 --> 00:32:19.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Dent it?

00:32:19.870 --> 00:32:20.786 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Dent it.

00:32:20.786 --> 00:32:21.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Gosh.

00:32:21.610 --> 00:32:24.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: In my book, I
talk about with this technology,

00:32:24.820 --> 00:32:28.030 align:middle line:84%
you could go super-luminal
speeds to, let's say,

00:32:28.030 --> 00:32:29.770 align:middle line:90%
Alpha Centauri.

00:32:29.770 --> 00:32:34.090 align:middle line:84%
If you had thrusters, Podkletnov
thrusters pushing you.

00:32:34.090 --> 00:32:36.310 align:middle line:90%
And you could go to 200c.

00:32:36.310 --> 00:32:38.862 align:middle line:84%
But you wouldn't feel
any inertial effects.

00:32:38.862 --> 00:32:40.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You wouldn't
have any G effects?

00:32:40.570 --> 00:32:43.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yeah,
because it's gravity waves.

00:32:43.690 --> 00:32:46.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Could we get up to
the speed of light with this?

00:32:46.120 --> 00:32:47.286 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: You could go--

00:32:47.286 --> 00:32:50.740 align:middle line:84%
I was suggesting, for
the first few months,

00:32:50.740 --> 00:32:54.730 align:middle line:84%
you'd go up to 80% of speed of
light with Brown's thrusters

00:32:54.730 --> 00:32:57.890 align:middle line:90%
which are very efficient.

00:32:57.890 --> 00:32:59.990 align:middle line:84%
Then you'd turn on your
Podkletnov thrusters

00:32:59.990 --> 00:33:04.550 align:middle line:84%
to go lightspeed, so I
speak, to use some terms

00:33:04.550 --> 00:33:05.510 align:middle line:90%
from science fiction.

00:33:05.510 --> 00:33:07.942 align:middle line:84%
You would end up
going up to 200c,

00:33:07.942 --> 00:33:11.600 align:middle line:84%
200 times the speed of light
when you're halfway there.

00:33:11.600 --> 00:33:14.630 align:middle line:84%
Then you turn your craft around,
and you start decelerating back

00:33:14.630 --> 00:33:16.710 align:middle line:90%
to normal speed.

00:33:16.710 --> 00:33:19.160 align:middle line:84%
So the whole thing could
be done in a couple months.

00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:20.201 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's dramatic.

00:33:20.201 --> 00:33:24.050 align:middle line:84%
We've got some video of this
incredible Russian genius.

00:33:24.050 --> 00:33:28.370 align:middle line:10%
>>EUGENE PODKLETNOV: If we speak
about new propulsion systems,

00:33:28.370 --> 00:33:34.670 align:middle line:10%
definitely these gravity
effects can be used.

00:33:34.670 --> 00:33:39.500 align:middle line:84%
And even at present, the
knowledge that we have,

00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:46.520 align:middle line:84%
if applied properly, can result
in very efficient propulsion

00:33:46.520 --> 00:33:51.260 align:middle line:84%
systems close to
what we call UFOs.

00:33:51.260 --> 00:33:57.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, in fact, I want to
believe that they exist.

00:33:57.530 --> 00:33:59.540 align:middle line:90%
And I have nothing against.

00:33:59.540 --> 00:34:03.410 align:middle line:84%
I have never seen
one in my life.

00:34:03.410 --> 00:34:06.380 align:middle line:84%
But from the experience
that we have,

00:34:06.380 --> 00:34:09.260 align:middle line:84%
it's possible to
make the objects that

00:34:09.260 --> 00:34:13.760 align:middle line:84%
will propagate in space using
modification of local gravity

00:34:13.760 --> 00:34:17.070 align:middle line:84%
field, using
polarization of vacuum.

00:34:17.070 --> 00:34:20.870 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of good
theoretical works in this field

00:34:20.870 --> 00:34:24.440 align:middle line:84%
and also a lot of
practical works.

00:34:24.440 --> 00:34:27.830 align:middle line:84%
But somehow this is
a forbidden area,

00:34:27.830 --> 00:34:34.179 align:middle line:84%
maybe because there are
some traditions in physics,

00:34:34.179 --> 00:34:38.679 align:middle line:84%
maybe because there are
some contradictions.

00:34:38.679 --> 00:34:45.460 align:middle line:84%
Also military organizations
are always interested in this.

00:34:45.460 --> 00:34:51.670 align:middle line:84%
And simply, if we speak
about anti-gravity platforms

00:34:51.670 --> 00:34:55.239 align:middle line:84%
or lifters or
whatever it is, people

00:34:55.239 --> 00:34:57.820 align:middle line:84%
say there are some
contradictions

00:34:57.820 --> 00:34:59.680 align:middle line:90%
with physical laws.

00:34:59.680 --> 00:35:01.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Paul, is
he still alive?

00:35:01.120 --> 00:35:02.078 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Oh, yeah.

00:35:02.078 --> 00:35:03.560 align:middle line:84%
I spoke to him
about a month ago.

00:35:03.560 --> 00:35:06.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is he still
doing dramatic things?

00:35:06.040 --> 00:35:08.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: He's working
more on his device that

00:35:08.380 --> 00:35:11.410 align:middle line:84%
spins, a superconducting
spinning disk that reduces

00:35:11.410 --> 00:35:13.925 align:middle line:90%
gravity for a things above it.

00:35:13.925 --> 00:35:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Where is he?

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:15.670 align:middle line:90%
Is he in Russia?

00:35:15.670 --> 00:35:17.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: In Finland,
he lives in Finland.

00:35:17.250 --> 00:35:18.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:35:18.050 --> 00:35:21.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I was
interested to use his impulse

00:35:21.070 --> 00:35:23.740 align:middle line:84%
beam to communicate,
send a message

00:35:23.740 --> 00:35:28.700 align:middle line:84%
to an extraterrestrial
communication beacon that is

00:35:28.700 --> 00:35:32.030 align:middle line:90%
sending us a message currently.

00:35:32.030 --> 00:35:34.060 align:middle line:84%
I discuss this in my
other book, "Decoding

00:35:34.060 --> 00:35:37.320 align:middle line:84%
the Message of the Pulsars,"
that we are being sent messages

00:35:37.320 --> 00:35:38.120 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:35:38.120 --> 00:35:39.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But we're not
decoding them, are we?

00:35:39.700 --> 00:35:41.366 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: SETI
hasn't done anything,

00:35:41.366 --> 00:35:44.120 align:middle line:84%
because they've been looking
for frequencies, regular radio

00:35:44.120 --> 00:35:44.920 align:middle line:90%
stations.

00:35:44.920 --> 00:35:45.610 align:middle line:90%
And these aren't.

00:35:45.610 --> 00:35:46.810 align:middle line:90%
They're pulses coming from--

00:35:46.810 --> 00:35:48.185 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you
talked to SETI?

00:35:48.185 --> 00:35:50.440 align:middle line:84%
I know Seth Shostak would--
do they listen to you?

00:35:50.440 --> 00:35:52.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: I
spoke with Shostak.

00:35:52.090 --> 00:35:53.450 align:middle line:90%
I had written my book.

00:35:53.450 --> 00:35:55.640 align:middle line:84%
I was willing to
send him a free copy.

00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:57.710 align:middle line:90%
And he didn't want to see it.

00:35:57.710 --> 00:35:58.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Gosh.

00:35:58.980 --> 00:36:00.520 align:middle line:90%
He knows better than that.

00:36:00.520 --> 00:36:03.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: He required
me to publish first

00:36:03.210 --> 00:36:04.710 align:middle line:90%
before he would even look.

00:36:04.710 --> 00:36:07.770 align:middle line:84%
I consider that
extremely arrogant.

00:36:07.770 --> 00:36:09.860 align:middle line:90%
I did publish finally.

00:36:09.860 --> 00:36:13.670 align:middle line:84%
Two years ago, I did publish
on this in a technical journal.

00:36:13.670 --> 00:36:16.190 align:middle line:90%
OK, so it's now published.

00:36:16.190 --> 00:36:18.110 align:middle line:84%
I haven't been
contacted by SETI.

00:36:18.110 --> 00:36:19.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's very
possible that if they

00:36:19.970 --> 00:36:22.820 align:middle line:84%
started listening
to you, we could be

00:36:22.820 --> 00:36:24.404 align:middle line:90%
communicating with an ET race.

00:36:24.404 --> 00:36:25.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It's
very important,

00:36:25.820 --> 00:36:29.780 align:middle line:84%
because they're informing
us about a wave of particles

00:36:29.780 --> 00:36:32.450 align:middle line:84%
that are coming towards
us this very minute.

00:36:32.450 --> 00:36:35.000 align:middle line:84%
And we're overdue
for the arrival.

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:36.230 align:middle line:90%
It's called the superwave.

00:36:36.230 --> 00:36:38.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, what
happens when that hits?

00:36:38.780 --> 00:36:40.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Biblical
Apocalypse, basically.

00:36:40.920 --> 00:36:41.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:36:41.720 --> 00:36:42.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Yes.

00:36:42.620 --> 00:36:43.995 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Paul,
are you telling me

00:36:43.995 --> 00:36:46.160 align:middle line:84%
that we're on the
verge of an apocalypse?

00:36:46.160 --> 00:36:49.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: It's not
certain, because these waves

00:36:49.790 --> 00:36:52.190 align:middle line:90%
can have different intensities.

00:36:52.190 --> 00:36:54.470 align:middle line:84%
I believe there was
one 700 years ago that

00:36:54.470 --> 00:36:55.790 align:middle line:90%
may have lasted a day.

00:36:55.790 --> 00:36:59.580 align:middle line:84%
And they see it in
the ice core record.

00:36:59.580 --> 00:37:02.900 align:middle line:84%
For example, it affected
the weather, crops.

00:37:02.900 --> 00:37:05.780 align:middle line:84%
But if it's a very intense
one, it can last 1,000 years.

00:37:05.780 --> 00:37:06.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, my god.

00:37:06.680 --> 00:37:08.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE:
Continually bombarding

00:37:08.180 --> 00:37:11.300 align:middle line:84%
the Earth and particles coming
into our magnetic field,

00:37:11.300 --> 00:37:14.690 align:middle line:84%
reducing the magnetic field of
the Earth, because when you get

00:37:14.690 --> 00:37:16.145 align:middle line:84%
particles in the
radiation belts,

00:37:16.145 --> 00:37:18.980 align:middle line:84%
they exert a magnetic
field opposed to the Earth.

00:37:18.980 --> 00:37:20.900 align:middle line:84%
So the field is
going to decrease.

00:37:20.900 --> 00:37:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And it could reverse,
just like what

00:37:22.400 --> 00:37:24.680 align:middle line:84%
happened during the
Neanderthal extinction.

00:37:24.680 --> 00:37:26.255 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is anybody
listening to you?

00:37:26.255 --> 00:37:28.380 align:middle line:84%
When you talk about these
incredible things-- and I

00:37:28.380 --> 00:37:31.550 align:middle line:84%
don't mean on a program like
this or "Coast to Coast."

00:37:31.550 --> 00:37:35.360 align:middle line:84%
But I mean are scientists
listening to you?

00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:37.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: You get
very little feedback.

00:37:37.610 --> 00:37:42.350 align:middle line:84%
But I am continually
contacted by investigators.

00:37:42.350 --> 00:37:44.720 align:middle line:84%
But you're talking about
the traditional ones

00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:45.580 align:middle line:90%
in the universities?

00:37:45.580 --> 00:37:45.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY:

00:37:45.620 --> 00:37:46.340 align:middle line:84%
>>PAUL LAVIOLETTE:
Yeah, who would say,

00:37:46.340 --> 00:37:47.424 align:middle line:90%
this guy's onto something.

00:37:47.424 --> 00:37:48.798 align:middle line:84%
>>LAVIOLETTE: Some
of them, yeah.

00:37:48.798 --> 00:37:50.204 align:middle line:84%
In fact, in the
military, there's

00:37:50.204 --> 00:37:51.620 align:middle line:84%
people there that
